A parallelogram has consecutive sides of length 10 and 15. 
The height to the side of length 10 is 12. Find the height 
to the side of length 15.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 (A) at (0,0);
 (B) at (7.5,0);
 (C) at (10.5,6);
 (D) at (3,6);


 (A) – (B) – (C) – (D) – cycle;

 % Height to base 15
 (D) – (3,0);
 (3,0.4) – (3.4,0.4) – (3.4,0);

 at (3.75,0) {15};
 at (1.5,3) {10};
 at (3.2,3) {12};
 at (6.75,3) {10};
 at (6.75,6) {15};
tikzpicture
